{"timestamp": "2025-12-16 15:24:35.634992", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Network Diagnostic Report – Mini‑Internet (RIP‑based)**  \\n\\n| Item | Observation | Assessment |\\n|------|-------------|------------|\\n| **Host‑to‑Host Connectivity** | `host_1` ↔ `host_2` ping: 4/4 packets, 0\\u202f% loss, avg RTT\\u202f≈\\u202f2.4\\u202fms | **Normal** – both hosts can reach each other with low latency. |\\n| **Host ↔ Web Server** | `host_1` → `web_server_1_1` (20.0.0.3) ping: 0\\u202f% loss, avg RTT\\u202f≈\\u202f3\\u202fms. <br> `host_2` → `web_server_1_1` ping: 0\\u202f% loss, avg RTT\\u202f≈\\u202f2.9\\u202fms | **Normal** – web servers are reachable from both internal hosts. |\\n| **Host ↔ VPN Server** | `host_1` → `vpn_server_1` (20.0.0.2) ping: 0\\u202f% loss, avg RTT\\u202f≈\\u202f3\\u202fms. <br> `host_2` → `vpn_server_1` ping: 0\\u202f% loss, avg RTT\\u202f≈\\u202f2.6\\u202fms | **Normal** – VPN server is reachable from both hosts. |\\n| **WireGuard Status on `host_1`** | `wg0` is up, public key present, listening port\\u202f45398. <br> Peer endpoint: 20.0.0.2:51820, allowed‑ips\\u202f172.16.1.0/24. | **Normal** – the tunnel is established and the allowed‑IP subnet is correctly advertised. |\\n| **Routing Tables** | All routers (router1, router2, gateway_router, external_router_1) have RIP‑derived routes for every internal subnet (10.0.0.0/24 – 10.0.3.0/24) and for the external 20.0.0.0/24 network. <br> No missing or duplicate routes were found. | **Normal** – routing tables are complete and consistent. |\\n| **Interface Status** | All `eth0` interfaces on hosts and all `eth0/eth1/eth2/eth3` on routers are `UP` and `LOWER_UP`. | **Normal** – no interface outages. |\\n| **Firewall / NAT** | `external_router_1` has no restrictive iptables rules (policy ACCEPT on all chains). | **Normal** – no unintended filtering. |\\n| **Web Server Response Times** | `curl` to `http://20.0.0.3` from both hosts: total time\\u202f≈\\u202f2\\u202fms (3 trials). | **Normal** – HTTP responses are instantaneous, indicating no bottleneck. |\\n| **VPN Tunnel Traffic** | `host_1` has a `wg0` interface with IP\\u202f172.16.1.11/24. Traffic to 172.16.1.0/24 is routed over the tunnel. | **Normal** – the tunnel is functional; no leakage to other hosts is observed. |\\n\\n### Summary of Findings\\n- **All ping tests succeed with 0\\u202f% packet loss and sub‑5\\u202fms RTTs.**  \\n- **Web servers are reachable from both internal hosts,** indicating that the external router’s forwarding and RIP routes are correctly installed.  \\n- **VPN server is reachable from both hosts,** and `host_1` has a fully‑configured WireGuard interface that can reach the 172.16.1.0/24 subnet.  \\n- **Routing tables on every router contain the expected RIP‑derived entries** for all internal and external subnets; no duplicate or missing routes were detected.  \\n- **No firewall or NAT rules are blocking traffic** on the external router or any other node.  \\n- **All interfaces are up and operational** with the expected MTU and queue disciplines.\\n\\n### Conclusion\\nThe current state of the mini‑Internet is **healthy and fully functional**. No connectivity, routing, or firewall anomalies were detected during the tests performed. All components (hosts, routers, VPN, and web servers) are operating as designed. No further action is required at this time., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='71b8ceff-0b7c-4d66-8b84-3745c772bc56'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
